# Wrangler static-assets upload excludes for the alloflow-cdn Workers deploy.
# (Cloudflare build runs `npx wrangler deploy` with assets directory "." = repo root;
# wrangler reads this file from the assets root, .gitignore syntax.)
#
# WHY: Workers assets have a hard 25 MiB/file limit. desktop/web-app/public/
# video_studio/vendor/ffmpeg/core/ffmpeg-core.wasm is 30.7 MiB, which failed the
# entire deploy and froze the CDN (2026-07-05). The desktop/web-app/ tree is the
# district-configured Firebase-hosted React app (which has no such
# limit) - the CDN only serves REPO-ROOT module files, and nothing references
# alloflow-cdn.pages.dev/desktop/web-app/... or /desktop/... (verified by grep).
# node_modules exists in the build clone after npm ci and would waste most of the
# 20,000-file assets budget.
node_modules/
desktop/web-app/
desktop/
